---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '@/components/PageHero.astro';
import QuotationRequest from '@/components/home/QuotationRequest.astro';

const country = "Rwanda";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Transformer in ${country} | Elsan Transformers`}
  description={`Premier transformer solutions and power infrastructure for ${country}.`}
>
  <PageHero 
    title={`Transformer in ${country}`}
    subtitle={`Powering ${country}'s grid with high-efficiency distribution and power transformers.`}
    backgroundImage="https://cdn.pagesmith.app/3ebbed7b/images/IMG-20260226-WA0075-640-640.webp"
  />
  
  <section class="py-16 bg-white" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:section1">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:i99brq">
      <div class="prose max-w-none prose-slate prose-lg" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:i99brr">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:4kvc59">Power Solutions for Rwanda</h2>
        
        <p data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:h0xucy">Elsan Transformer supplies certified power and distribution transformers to Rwanda, manufactured in Turkey to IEC 60076 and ISO 9001:2015 standards, with export logistics via Mombasa and Dar es Salaam ports to Kigali.</p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:43tp06">Rwanda's Electricity Sector and Transformer Requirements</h3>
        <p data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:h0xucz">Rwanda has achieved some of the fastest electricity access growth in sub-Saharan Africa. REG (Rwanda Energy Group) and its subsidiary EUCL (Energy Utility Corporation Limited) manage generation, transmission, and distribution across a grid serving Kigali, Musanze, Huye, Rubavu, and all thirty districts. RURA (Rwanda Utilities Regulatory Authority) governs technical standards, including transformer specifications. Rwanda's Vision 2050 commitment to 100% electricity access drives ongoing capital investment in grid infrastructure, substation construction, and off-grid solar deployment across the country's highland terrain.</p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:43tp07">Elsan's Transformer Range for Rwanda</h3>
        <p data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:h0xud0">Elsan supplies the complete range of units required by REG, EUCL, contractors, and project developers across Rwanda:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:nq91v"><strong>Distribution transformers:</strong> 25 kVA to 2,500 kVA — for Rwanda's 11 kV and 33 kV medium-voltage network in pole-mounted and pad-mounted configurations</li>
          <li data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:nq92h"><strong>Power transformers:</strong> 3.15 MVA to 50 MVA — for substation construction and grid reinforcement under REG's capital investment programme</li>
          <li data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:nq92i"><strong>Single-phase units:</strong> up to 160 kVA — for rural electrification across Rwanda's thirty districts</li>
          <li data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:nq92j"><strong>Solar PV transformers:</strong> custom step-up units engineered for Rwanda's growing solar IPP and off-grid sector</li>
        </ul>

        <p data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:h0xud1">Rwanda's altitude — with most of the country between 1,500 and 2,500 metres above sea level — is a critical transformer specification factor. Elsan's engineering team applies IEC 60076 altitude correction requirements to insulation levels, dielectric testing voltages, and cooling ratings, ensuring all units delivered to Rwanda perform to full specification in highland operating conditions. Factory routine testing is completed on every unit before dispatch.</p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:43tp08">Standards, Certifications, and Documentation</h3>
        <p data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:h0xud2">Elsan holds ISO 9001:2015, ISO 14001, and ISO 45001 certification. All products comply with IEC 60076. Routine test certificates, type test reports, and technical datasheets accompany every order — meeting RURA regulatory requirements and World Bank, AfDB, or bilateral donor documentation standards.</p>

        <div class="mt-16 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:i99bro">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:4kvc57">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
          <div class="space-y-8" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:i99brp">
            <div data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:i99brq">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:43tp09">Does Elsan supply altitude-corrected transformers for Rwanda?</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:h0xud3">Yes — highland insulation derating to IEC 60076 is applied as standard for all installations across Rwanda's terrain.</p>
            </div>
            <div data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:i99brr">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:43tp0a">How are units delivered?</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600" data-ps="src/pages/transformer-in-rwanda.astro:h0xud4">Via Mombasa or Dar es Salaam port with full export documentation and logistics support to Kigali.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <QuotationRequest />
</BaseLayout>
